article.description: — Trazarien White's 25 points helped UNC Wilmington defeat Charleston (SC) 80-74 on Thursday night.
article.headline: White scores 25 as UNC Wilmington downs Charleston (SC) 80-74
article.linkText: White scores 25 as UNC Wilmington downs Charleston (SC) 80-74
article.story: CHARLESTON, S.C. -- — Trazarien White's 25 points helped UNC Wilmington defeat Charleston (SC) 80-74 on Thursday night. White had nine rebounds for the Seahawks (15-6, 6-3 Coastal Athletic Association). Shykeim Phillips scored 15 points while shooting 7 of 12 from the field and 1 for 3 from the line, and added six rebounds. Donovan Newby and Nolan Hodge both finished with 11. Kobe Rodgers led the Cougars (15-7, 6-3) in scoring, finishing with 20 points. Reyne Smith added 18 points for Charleston (SC). Ben Burnham also had 11 points and seven rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
